#patch using diff file
patch < patchfile.diff

# reverse patch
patch -R < patchfile.diff

# specify strip level
The strip level indicates how many leading components of the file paths in the patch file should be removed.
patch -p1 < patchfile.diff

# from arch wiki page on st
To apply a patch, download the diff and apply it with patch -i patch.diff.
This alters the default config file config.def.h; if you are maintaining your own config.h, 
copy your configs from config.h into a copy of config.def.h and rename it config.h, then make clean install


